[2] Cholera - Angola (Huambo)
Date: Wed, 19 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=433901>

In the last 72 hours, 2 new cases of cholera were registered in
Longonjo village, about 64 km from Huambo city, sources with the
health services told ANGOP on Wed, 19 Apr 2006.
The director of health centre of Longonjo, Abel Chitongua, said that
the 2 patients, aged 16 and 22, suspected of having contracted the
illness, are from Benguela and Baja-Farta municipalities. The health
official stated that both patients are being treated.
Last weekend 2 people died at Londuimbali and Ukuma municipalities,
in Huambo province, both victims of cholera. The cholera outbreak has
already spread into the 6 provinces of the country, claiming 576 lives.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Another province reports in. On the Angola map, Huambo is located
bordering on the eastern end of Benguela.
