[3] Cholera - Angola (Malanje)
Date: Tue, 18 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=433506>

The province of Malanje already registered 25 deaths by cholera
between 30 Mar and 17 Apr 2006, it was announced on Mon, 17 Apr 2006
during a press conference.
According to the spokesman for the commission on prevention and
control of cholera, Andre Ribeiro, the number of patients increased
to 192, of whom 135 were discharged from hospital. On the other
hand, he added that, from this number 30 children have been
hospitalized, of whom 6 died and 15 were discharged.
Gaspar Neto, acting provincial governor, stressed that cholera cases
have been detected in the districts of Cacuso, Kalandula and in the
communes of Lombe and Quizenga.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The cholera outbreak continues to spread in Angola. As can be seen
on the map of this country, Malanje province has as part of its
western border Kwanza Norte.
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf> - Mod.LL]
