[5] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Tue, 18 Apr 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: AngolaPress [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=433601>

Of 340 new cases of cholera recorded in Luanda over the last 24
hours, 2 people died, raising the toll to 120 deaths since the
outbreak was declared in February 2006, an official source said.
The provincial director of Public Health, Vita Vemba, said priority
must be given to Cacuaco district, where the number of cases has been
on the rise over the last few days.
The sickness has spread to the provinces of Benguela, with 274
deaths, out of 3503 cases, Kwanza-Norte (51 deaths, of 1127 cases),
Bengo (49 deaths out of 378 cases) and Malanje (25 deaths out of 1378 cases).
