[6] Cholera - Angola (Benguela)
Date: Sun, 16 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=433018>

On Wed, 12 Apr 2006, 6 people who were hospitalized with cholera
symptoms in the Chongoroi Municipal Hospital, south Benguela
province, passed away, ANGOP learnt.
District health authorities revealed the scarcity of facilities for
the hospitalization of patients affected by the disease, to which
they appeal for the intervention of the Provincial Government in
order to stop the spread of the disease in the region.
Chongoroi is located 150 kilometers to the southeast of Benguela
city. As of Thu, 13 Apr 2006, Benguela Health services registered
2187 cholera cases and 199 deaths.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The district of Chongoroi is quite close to Cubal district, one of
those previously reported with cholera. - Mod.LL]
