[10] Cholera - Ghana (Accra)
Date: Mon, 17 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC Monitoring Africa [edited]
<http://www.redorbit.com/news/health/472611/ghanaian_health_body_alarmed_as_cholera_ravages_accra/index.html?source=r_health>

[Text of report entitled "GHS worried over 93 cholera cases recorded
in Accra" published by Ghanaian independent Joy FM radio on 16 Apr 2006]
The Ghana Health Service says the rising number of cholera cases in
parts of the Greater Accra region gives cause for concern. The
Service has recorded 93 cases alone in April 2006, compared to none
in 2005 over the same period.
The Greater Accra regional director of the GHS, Dr Edward Antwi told
JOYNEWS that the current prevalence of the disease can be traced to
the last outbreak from Sep through Dec 2005. He said although no
deaths have been recorded yet, the situation remains alarming. He
said, "with cholera, even one case is alarming. I mean cholera is one
of the notifiable diseases. When we say notifiable, it means that one
case is too many."
--
