[13] Cholera - Myanmar (Mandalay)
Date: Thu, 13 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Democreatic Voice of Burma [edited]
http://english.dvb.no/news.php?id=6840

Some young children have died from cholera in central Burma's
Mandalay, where the deadly avian flu H5N1 occurred recently. Local
residents told DVB that they are very concerned. Health staff also
told DVB that there has been an increase in the [numbers of] cases of
cholera in recent days.
As the cholera outbreak is occurring out of season, staff from
divisional health department have been carrying out field work and
tests and telling people to spray disinfectants around the areas affected.
A nurse who doesn't want to be identified said that most patients are
young children with severe diarrhea from poor wards in Kanthaya or
Pyigyitagun, where the hygiene is particularly poor due to acute
poverty. But another nurse from Mandalay general hospital said that
although she heard the reports, no patients have turned up at the hospital.
--
